// =============================================================================
// LOADING SCREEN TIPS -- Useless, Contradictory, and Satirical
// =============================================================================
//
// Displayed during room transitions and loading screens. Each tip should
// either be genuinely useless, self-contradictory, a PoE community meme
// reference, or a satirical jab at game design / tax law.
//
// These are shown one at a time with the "TIP:" prefix.
// Minimum 20 tips. Shuffled randomly, no repeats until all shown.
//
// "If you're reading this, you've been on the loading screen too long.
//  Working as intended."
// =============================================================================

LoadingTips(
    tips: [
        // --- Genuinely useless advice ---
        "Tip: To avoid dying, don't get hit.",
        "Tip: Enemies deal damage. This is by design.",
        "Tip: You can move in 8 directions. We counted.",
        "Tip: The dodge roll lets you dodge things. Hence the name.",
        "Tip: Items with better stats are generally better than items with worse stats.",

        // --- Self-contradictory / self-aware ---
        "Tip: The Passive Tree contains exactly one node that matters. Good luck.",
        "Tip: This tip intentionally left blank.",
        "Tip: The Tax Code is over 1,500 pages. You've read 0 of them. Don't worry, neither have we.",
        "Tip: Loading tips are a great way to disguise loading times. You're welcome.",
        "If you're reading this, you've been on the loading screen too long. Working as intended.",

        // --- PoE community memes ---
        "The Compliance Manifesto states: 'Easy combat reduces player suffering, and suffering is the point.'",
        "Patch 3.47: We've made the game harder. You're welcome.",
        "Fun fact: The word 'fun' does not appear anywhere in the Tax Code. This was an intentional design choice.",
        "Tip: 'Close your eyes and file' is not financial advice. It is, however, game advice.",
        "Remember: this is a buff.",
        "Tip: The drop rate for Premium Filing Fees has been adjusted. We will not tell you in which direction.",
        "Tip: Your build is wrong. We can't tell you how. But it is.",

        // --- Tax law satire ---
        "Did you know? In Taxeclast, tax evasion is a crime. Tax avoidance is a skill. The difference is your accountant.",
        "Tip: The Compliance Meter tracks how legally you're playing. Low compliance means better loot. Make of that what you will.",
        "Fun fact: The Bloated Filer has been Employee of the Month for 30 consecutive years. No one else applied.",
        "Tip: Commissioner Geonor's approval rating is 100%. Disapproval has been outlawed.",
        "Per Section 7(b)(iii): loading tips are tax-deductible if read during business hours.",
        "Tip: The IRS Agent that spawns when your Compliance is low is not a bug. It's a feature. An auditing feature.",

        // --- Game design self-awareness ---
        "Tip: The developers spent more time on these loading tips than on game balance.",
        "Tip: Somewhere in the Passive Tree, there's a node that gives +0.1% damage. It took 3 hours to implement.",
        "Tip: The Debate Club was originally a rhythm game. We changed it. You're welcome.",
        "Tip: If the combat doesn't feel good, try adjusting the screen shake slider. It won't help, but you'll feel like you tried.",
        "Tip: This game contains approximately 1,500 passive tree nodes. The developer who placed them is no longer with us. (They quit. They're fine.)",

        // --- Existential ---
        "Tip: Every enemy you kill was once an employee with a pension plan. You just eliminated their retirement.",
        "Tip: The Refund Witch's abilities are powered by pure tax law. This is somehow more terrifying than regular magic.",
        "Tip: In the land of Taxeclast, death is not the end. It's a reclassification event.",

        // --- Actually useful (buried among useless tips for comedy) ---
        "Tip: Recovery frames can be canceled into a dodge roll. This is the most important tip on this screen.",
        "Tip: Elite enemies with the 'Penalizing' prefix reflect 5% of damage. High-DPS builds should watch their own HP.",
        "Tip: Input buffering lets you queue your next action during the last 4 frames of an animation. Mash responsibly.",
    ],
)
